 Tests use `writeOutputContract` mock interception to mutate contract object in-place past `readonly` interface. Couples to implementation detail.\n- Tech debt: `readStateWithBody` returns mutable `HarnessState` — flag mutation relies on this mutability.\n- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 13, Edit: 11, Grep: 7). 7 unique files, 13 reads (workflow-engine.ts 5x, workflow-engine.test.ts 5x). No redundancy.\n\n### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — code-review (2026-04-03T18:20)\n\n- HIGH: Test AC#1 name claimed to test positive flag-setting but actually tested null/no-op path. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Duplicate AC#7 test names. Fixed with AC#7b rename.\n- MEDIUM: Bare catch block in `propagateVerifyFlags` swallowed error details. Fixed.\n- LOW (not fixed): Tests rely on in-place mutation of contract object inside mock. Coupling risk.\n- LOW (not fixed): No integration test for AC#6 (cross-module verify reads engine-set flags).\n- Coverage: 96.59% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 9, Edit: 4, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 7 unique files, 9 reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — verify (2026-04-03T18:25)\n\n- ALL_PASS: 8/8 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n- Verification gap: AC#6 proof is structural (confirms same field names read) — no E2E integration test.\n- `codeharness verify` warning about missing exec-plan — informational only.\n- 2 pre-existing lint warnings (prefer-const, unused error variable).\n- Build, tests, lint, coverage all pass.\n\nToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 3, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. Coverage run duplicated with test run.\n\n---\n\n### 16-3-telemetry-writer — create-story (2026-04-03T17:39)\n\n- No config.yaml found at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — workflow references it but doesn't exist. Not critical.\n- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent per instruction. Still shows backlog.\n- No web research needed — pure node:fs/node:path module.\n- `attempts` field gap — TaskContext doesn't include retry count. Telemetry will have `attempts: null` until future story extends TaskContext.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-3-telemetry-writer — dev-story (2026-04-03T17:44)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 18/18 tests pass, 26/26 existing tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Edit: 8, Write: 2). 5 unique files, 5 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-3-telemetry-writer — code-review (2026-04-03T17:55)\n\n- HIGH: `clearNullTaskRegistry` JSDoc claims it re-registers built-in handlers but does not. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `readTelemetryForEpic` defaulted to `process.cwd()` — made `projectDir` required.\n- MEDIUM: `TestResultsSummary` duplicated `TestResults` type. Fixed with type alias.\n- MEDIUM: Unused imports in test. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: null-task-registry.test.ts re-registered fake no-op instead of real handler. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM (pre-existing): stats.test.ts assertion mismatch. Fixed.\n- LOW (not fixed): `cost ?? null` is dead code (cost is never undefined).\n- LOW (not fixed): Unnecessary optional chain on `contract?.acceptanceCriteria`.\n- Coverage: 96.58% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n- 4737 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 35 tool calls (Bash: 20, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 13 reads. Ran coverage 3 times.\n\n### 16-3-telemetry-writer — verify (2026-04-03T18:06)\n\n- ALL_PASS: 10/10 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n- `codeharness verify` failed on documentation gate: AGENTS.md missing entries for telemetry-writer.ts and null-task-registry.ts. Not an AC issue.\n- Coverage: telemetry-writer.ts 100% Stmts, 93.75% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines.\n- Branch gap: line 86 catch block empty path in readTelemetryForEpic uncovered (minor).\n- 30 pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files.\n\nToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Write: 1). 4 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — create-story (2026-04-03T16:39)\n\n- Config file at `_bmad/config.yaml` not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` as workflow implied\n- No `project-context.md` exists in repo — skipped\n- Decomposed bundled epic ACs into 11 separate ACs for testability\n- Added ACs #9 (flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity), #10 (agent: null), #11 (scope: per-epic) — implied by architecture but not explicit in epic\n- Risk: `additionalProperties: false` in schema requires careful extension\n- Risk: `oneOf` for flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity may be complex with Ajv — simpler to validate in TypeScript\n- All 11 ACs tagged `test-provable`\n\nToken Report: 23 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — dev-story (2026-04-03T16:48)\n\n- Pre-existing test failure: `commands/__tests__/stats.test.ts` — unrelated to this story\n- Pre-existing TS errors in `run.test.ts`, `issue.test.ts`, `verdict-parser.test.ts` — unrelated\n- Used Python script for bulk-replace of ~60 inline workflow objects in `workflow-engine.test.ts` with `makeWorkflow()` wrappers\n- Schema vs code enforcement: `flow`/`story_flow` mutual exclusivity enforced in parser code, not JSON Schema `oneOf` (draft-07 creates confusing errors)\n- `execution` object has `additionalProperties: false` — future config additions require schema changes\n- 4676 tests passed, 1 pre-existing failure\n\nToken Report: 33 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 11, Edit: 15, Grep: 5, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 14 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — code-review (2026-04-03T16:57)\n\n- HIGH: `resolveHierarchicalFlow` accepted arbitrary types without validation — could produce malformed objects. Fixed with `resolveExecutionConfig()` and `normalizeFlowArray()`.\n- MEDIUM: Operator precedence issue in `workflow-parser.ts` with `as` cast + `??`. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `run.ts` null guard used `!== null` instead of `!= null`. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: 4 missing test cases for loop blocks and strategy validation error paths. Added.\n- LOW (not fixed): Duplicate `flow`/`story_flow` coexistence check in two files (defense-in-depth).\n- LOW (not fixed): `resolveHierarchicalFlow` silently returns empty storyFlow when no flow provided.\n- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` command is broken (pre-existing coverage parser bug).\n- Tests: 28 → 43 (+15 new). 4691 passed, 1 pre-existing failure.\n\nToken Report: 28 tool calls (Bash: 16, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. ~4 redundant Bash calls trying to parse coverage output.\n\n### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — verify (2026-04-03T17:05)\n\n- ALL_PASS: 11/11 ACs verified with test evidence\n- `codeharness verify` initially failed on preconditions: AGENTS.md missing `hierarchical-flow.ts`, proof format headers wrong (`### AC #N:` vs `## AC N:`)\n- Fixed: AGENTS.md entries for `hierarchical-flow.ts` and `drivers.ts`, proof header format, session state flags\n- Pre-existing: `stats.test.ts` failure, lint 1 error + 52 warnings (all outside story scope)\n- Coverage: `hierarchical-flow.ts` at 100% across all metrics\n- Redundancy: Coverage run executed 3 times with different grep filters before usable output\n\nToken Report (verify subagent): 17 tool calls (Bash: 11, Read: 3, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 4 unique files. Coverage run redundancy.\nToken Report (fix subagent): ~46 tool calls. Fixed AGENTS.md, proof format, state flags.\n\n### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — create-story (2026-04-03T17:10)\n\n- No `project-context.md` file exists in the repo. Not a blocker.\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path in workflow.yaml is inaccurate — actual is `_bmad/config.yaml`\n- Risk: AC #6 (<10ms performance) may be flaky in CI under load — should use generous threshold\n- `checkDriverHealth()` needs null-agent skip — if missed, engine will try to instantiate driver for null tasks\n- run.ts fix for null agents already done in story 16-1 (line 141). Task 3 is verification-only.\n- All 8 ACs tagged test-provable\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Read: 11, Grep: 2, Glob: 4, Bash: 3, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 13 unique files, 13 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — dev-story (2026-04-03T17:17)\n\n- Workaround: `executeNullTask` throws plain `EngineError` object (not Error subclass) for NULL_TASK_NOT_FOUND. Added `isEngineError()` type guard. Inconsistent with `DispatchError` which extends Error. Future cleanup should make EngineError a proper Error subclass.\n- Code quality: Null task branches in `executeWorkflow()` and `executeLoopBlock()` duplicate scope-handling logic. Could be refactored to generic \"execute task for scope\" function.\n- Edge case: `cost` field in `TaskContext` only carries forward previous task's `cost_usd`, not accumulated total. Story spec says \"total cost so far\" but engine doesn't track cumulative cost.\n- run.ts line 141 already has null agent guard from 16-1 — no changes needed (Task 3 verified).\n- 4712 tests passed, 1 pre-existing failure (stats.test.ts). All 21 new tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 11, Edit: 7, Grep: 3, Write: 3, Glob: 1). 10 unique files, 14 total reads (workflow-engine.ts 5x due to size). No redundancy.\n\n### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — code-review (2026-04-03T17:24)\n\n- HIGH: `success: false` from null task handler silently ignored — checkpoint written as success. Fixed with EngineError NULL_TASK_FAILED.\n- MEDIUM: Handler exceptions not wrapped in EngineError. Fixed with NULL_TASK_HANDLER_ERROR code.\n- MEDIUM: `cost` field used last task's cost instead of accumulated total. Fixed with `accumulatedCostUsd` tracker.\n- MEDIUM: No registry cleanup function for test isolation. Fixed with `clearNullTaskRegistry()`.\n- MEDIUM: Missing failure path tests. Added 5 new test cases.\n- LOW (not fixed): `executeNullTask` accepts `task` param but doesn't use it — misleading API surface.\n- LOW (not fixed): Duplicated null-task-path code in executeWorkflow/executeLoopBlock.\n- Coverage: `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` broken due to pre-existing stats.test.ts failure preventing coverage generation.\n- Architecture: accumulated cost tracking is bolt-on threading rather than structural ExecutionContext.\n\nToken Report: 37 tool calls (Bash: 18, Read: 12, Edit: 10, Grep: 7, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 14 reads (workflow-engine.ts 5x). Two full test suite runs.\n\n### 16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks — verify (2026-04-03T17:30)\n\n- ALL_PASS: 8/8 ACs verified with test evidence\n- `codeharness verify` failed on bookkeeping (tests_passed=false, coverage_met=false, AGENTS.md stale) — not actual AC failures\n- Coverage: null-task-registry.ts at 100% (statements/branches/functions/lines)\n- Verification gap: executeNullTask() coverage in workflow-engine.ts not separately measured (tested via 17 integration tests)\n- Pre-existing: stats.test.ts failure, lint require-yield error in workflow-engine.test.ts\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 1, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 1 unique file. Coverage run twice (first without filter).\n\n---\n\n### 16-5-coverage-deduplication — create-story (2026-04-03T18:28)\n\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` does not exist — config variables unresolvable. Used defaults.\n- No `project-context.md` found in repo.\n- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent per instruction.\n- Risk: `outputContract.testResults` is currently always `null` (hardcoded in engine). Coverage deduplication logic testable via unit tests but won't activate in real workflow runs until engine gains test result parsing. Fallback path (AC #3) handles this.\n- Risk: `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` is a static function with no parameters — extending it to accept coverage context requires signature change.\n- All 6 ACs tagged `test-provable`.\n\nToken Report: 24 tool calls (Read: 7, Grep: 10, Glob: 5, Bash: 1, Write: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-5-coverage-deduplication — dev-story (2026-04-03T18:35)\n\n- `dispatchTask` integration tests for prompt verification are weak — mock setup makes it difficult to inspect exact prompt the driver receives. Unit tests on `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext` provide better coverage of the actual logic.\n- `testResults` field is still always `null` in engine-built contracts (hardcoded). Coverage dedup will only activate once engine gains test result parsing from agent output.\n- `skipIfMet` parameter on `runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage` is not yet called from production code. Engine-level dedup happens via prompt context (Task 3), not by calling `runCoverage(dir, true)`. Skip logic in runner available for future use.\n- 4768 tests pass (21 new).\n\nToken Report: 29 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 16, Edit: 9, Grep: 4, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 15 unique files, 20 total reads (workflow-engine.ts 4x due to size). No other redundancy.\n\n### 16-5-coverage-deduplication — code-review (2026-04-03T18:42)\n\n- HIGH: Vacuous integration test assertions — `if` guards silently skip assertions when mock produces no calls. Fixed with explicit `expect().toBeDefined()` + unconditional assertions.\n- MEDIUM: Duplicated skip logic in runner.ts — copy-pasted between `runCoverage()` and `checkOnlyCoverage()`. Fixed: extracted `checkSkipIfMet()` helper.\n- MEDIUM: Duplicated format string between evaluator.ts and workflow-engine.ts. Fixed: extracted `formatCoverageContextMessage()`.\n- LOW (not fixed): `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext` doesn't independently verify `failed === 0` — relies on upstream invariant.\n- LOW (not fixed): Synthetic `CoverageResult` returns `passCount: 0, failCount: 0` — misleading but unused.\n- LOW (not fixed): Redundant disk read in `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext` when flag already in memory.\n- Coverage: 96.6% overall, all 176 files above 80% floor.\n- 4768 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 7, Read: 9, Edit: 6, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 12 reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-5-coverage-deduplication — verify (2026-04-03T18:48)\n\n- ALL_PASS: 6/6 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n- Proof document required rewrite to match `codeharness verify` expected format (`## AC N:` headers with evidence blocks).\n- AC#5 evidence slightly indirect — verified `checkPreconditions()` doesn't import/call `runCoverage`, but test checks flag-based pass/fail not call stack absence.\n- Pre-existing lint: 1 error in `run.test.ts`, 53 warnings — none in story files.\n- `codeharness verify` warnings about showboat and exec-plan expected for local CLI verification.\n- 4768 tests pass, coverage 96.6%.\n\nToken Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 4, Grep: 9, Write: 2, Glob: 1). 3 unique files, 4 reads. Lint and coverage each run twice — could combine.\n\n---\n\n### 16-6-story-flow-execution — create-story (2026-04-03T18:55)\n\n- Workflow template file (`workflow.md`) did not exist — adapted to follow `instructions.xml` directives.\n- Skipped web research and validation checklist interactive loop (autonomous mode).\n- Risk: Circuit breaker halts during loop means telemetry null tasks won't execute — documented as expected.\n- Risk: grep for `workflow.flow` consumers beyond engine could reveal unexpected references.\n- Observation: simplest story in epic 16 — essentially a one-line property rename plus tests.\n- All 6 ACs tagged `test-provable`.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 6, Grep: 6, Write: 1, Glob: 5, Skill: 1). 8 unique files, 8 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-6-story-flow-execution — dev-story (2026-04-03T18:58)\n\nNone. Clean implementation — 2-line engine change, 11 new tests, 4779 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 8, Edit: 5, Grep: 4, Glob: 3, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files, 9 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 16-6-story-flow-execution — code-review (2026-04-03T19:02)\n\n- HIGH: Verdict JSON delivered via `subagentResult` instead of `text` events in 3 tests. Engine ignores `subagentResult`; `parseVerdict` received wrong input. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: AC #2 \"telemetry after loop\" test had no loop; tested sequential ordering only. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: AC #3 assertions trivially true (`> 1`, `toBeDefined()`); did not verify actual iteration count. Fixed.\n- LOW (not fixed): `defaultExecution` constant duplicates `EXECUTION_DEFAULTS` from `hierarchical-flow.ts`.\n- LOW (not fixed): `setupDefaultMocks()` default `text: 'Done'` causes `parseVerdict('Done')` to throw in any test that doesn't override.\n- Coverage: 96.63% overall, all 176 files above 80% floor.\n- 4780 tests pass, 0 failures.\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 9, Edit: 4, Grep: 7, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 7 unique files, 11 reads (workflow-engine.ts 4x, story-flow-execution.test.ts 3x).\n\n### 16-6-story-flow-execution — verify (2026-04-03T19:10)\n\n- Initial proof format wrong (`### AC N:` vs `## AC N:`). Rewrote.\n- All ACs verified via unit tests (mock driver/circuit breaker). Appropriate for test-provable tier.\n- Lint: 1 error + 53 warnings, all pre-existing in unrelated files.\n- 4780 tests pass, coverage 96.61%.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 4, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 4 unique files. Lint run twice, coverage run twice.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":4,"newStart":1,"newLines":4,"lines":["-# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 4)","+# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 7)"," "," ## Prior Sessions (Summary)"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
