{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MhSojYxQi6QD3G7L9MYQcx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file is created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-1-worktree-manager.md`.\n\n**Summary:** Auto-discovered story `17-1-worktree-manager` (first backlog story in Epic 17). Created a comprehensive story file with 11 acceptance criteria covering:\n- `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` -- branch creation, worktree creation, path return\n- `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` -- worktree removal, branch deletion, idempotency\n- `listWorktrees()` -- porcelain parsing, filtering by prefix\n- `detectOrphans()` -- orphaned worktree detection\n- Error handling, stale state cleanup, NFR compliance (10s timeout, branch prefix)\n\nEach AC has a verification tier tag. 9 of 11 are `test-provable` (can mock `execSync`), 1 is `runtime-provable` (NFR1 timing), 1 covers the codeharness prefix convention (`test-provable`).\n\nDid NOT: modify sprint-status.yaml, git add, or git commit (as instructed).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No project-context.md found** -- globbing for `**/project-context.md` returned no results. Used other artifacts (architecture, epics, previous story) for project context instead.\n- **Merge excluded from scope** -- The epic AC says \"worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup\" but architecture Decision 1 explicitly puts merge in Story 18-1. I scoped this story to create/cleanup/list/orphan-detect only, matching the epic's AC list. The story description still says \"merge\" for traceability but tasks/ACs do not include it.\n- **Orphan detection heuristic** -- AC #8 defines orphans as worktrees without an active PID in lane-state.json. The lane-state.json format isn't defined yet (that's a Story 17-2 concern). The dev agent may need to define a minimal PID-tracking convention or simplify to \"worktree exists but no lock file.\"\n- **Slug sanitization** -- Not explicitly called out in the epic's ACs but added as an edge case in dev notes. Branch names with special characters from epic names could break git commands.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Read: 9, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Bash: 1, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git log --oneline -6` (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: the two Glob calls for `create-story/*` and `create-story/**/*` returned overlapping results -- could have used a single `**/*` pattern."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afc19ee3704ef682d (use SendMessage with to: 'afc19ee3704ef682d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69088\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 160392</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"187035da-d60e-40cf-8aef-09e6134be246","uuid":"d348244a-135e-44c9-ad99-6fc8094bd450","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:23:21.080Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-create-story for story 17-1-worktree-manager. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n\nDefault to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"afc19ee3704ef682d","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file is created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-1-worktree-manager.md`.\n\n**Summary:** Auto-discovered story `17-1-worktree-manager` (first backlog story in Epic 17). Created a comprehensive story file with 11 acceptance criteria covering:\n- `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` -- branch creation, worktree creation, path return\n- `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` -- worktree removal, branch deletion, idempotency\n- `listWorktrees()` -- porcelain parsing, filtering by prefix\n- `detectOrphans()` -- orphaned workt