{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pph2sRQFTaD6XkYHKLm8od","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 17.1: Worktree Manager\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup,\n9\tso that parallel epics run in isolated working directories.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` exists, **when** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **then** it creates a git branch named `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` from the current HEAD of the main branch. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the branch is created, **then** it creates a git worktree at `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId}` pointing to the new branch and returns the absolute worktree path. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the operation completes, **then** the total wall-clock time is under 10 seconds (NFR1). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** a worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the worktree is removed via `git worktree remove` and the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` is deleted via `git branch -D`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"187035da-d60e-40cf-8aef-09e6134be246","uuid":"56b983ed-9e77-45af-b2e2-88707e4213ca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:23:52.387Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-1-worktree-manager.md","content":"# Story 17.1: Worktree Manager\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup,\nso that parallel epics run in isolated working directories.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` exists, **when** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **then** it creates a git branch named `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` from the current HEAD of the main branch. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the branch is created, **then** it creates a git worktree at `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId}` pointing to the new branch and returns the absolute worktree path. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the operation completes, **then** the total wall-clock time is under 10 seconds (NFR1). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** a worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the worktree is removed via `git worktree remove` and the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` is deleted via `git branch -D`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n","numLines":20,"startLine":1,"totalLines":206}}}
