{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLojxm1tp4h4XeNw4W8mzJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 17.1: Worktree Manager\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup,\n9\tso that parallel epics run in isolated working directories.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` exists, **when** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **then** it creates a git branch named `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` from the current HEAD of the main branch. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the branch is created, **then** it creates a git worktree at `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId}` pointing to the new branch and returns the absolute worktree path. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called, **when** the operation completes, **then** the total wall-clock time is under 10 seconds (NFR1). <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** a worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the worktree is removed via `git worktree remove` and the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` is deleted via `git branch -D`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` is called, **when** no worktree exists for that epicId, **then** the function completes without error (idempotent). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** `listWorktrees()` is called, **when** one or more codeharness worktrees exist, **then** it returns an array of `WorktreeInfo` objects containing `epicId`, `path`, `branch`, and `createdAt` for every worktree whose branch starts with `codeharness/epic-`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** `listWorktrees()` is called, **when** no codeharness worktrees exist, **then** it returns an empty array. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** orphaned worktrees from a previous crashed run exist (worktree directory present but no active codeharness process), **when** `detectOrphans()` is called, **then** it returns an array of orphaned `WorktreeInfo` entries whose worktree paths are present on disk but not tracked by any running codeharness process. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** `createWorktree` is called, **when** the branch `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` already exists (stale from a crash), **then** the function cleans up the stale branch and worktree before re-creating, rather than throwing. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** `createWorktree` is called, **when** the git command fails (e.g., not a git repo, disk full), **then** a descriptive `WorktreeError` is thrown with the stderr from the git command, and any partially-created branch or worktree is cleaned up. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t11. **Given** all git operations in worktree-manager, **when** they execute, **then** stderr is captured and included in error messages, and branch names are prefixed with `codeharness/` to avoid collision with user branches (NFR12). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` with types and interfaces (AC: #1, #2, #6, #8, #11)\n38\t  - [ ] Define `WorktreeInfo` interface: `epicId`, `path`, `branch`, `createdAt`\n39\t  - [ ] Define `WorktreeError` error class extending `Error` with `stderr` field\n40\t  - [ ] Define `WorktreeManager` class with constructor accepting `mainBranch: string` (default `'main'`)\n41\t  - [ ] Constants: `BRANCH_PREFIX = 'codeharness/epic-'`, `WORKTREE_BASE = '/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-'`\n42\t\n43\t- [ ] Task 2: Implement `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #9, #10)\n44\t  - [ ] Run `git branch codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug} {mainBranch}` via `execSync`\n45\t  - [ ] Run `git worktree add /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId} codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}` via `execSync`\n46\t  - [ ] On branch-already-exists: call cleanup first, then retry create (AC #9)\n47\t  - [ ] On any failure: clean up partial state (remove worktree if created, delete branch if created)\n48\t  - [ ] Wrap git stderr in `WorktreeError`\n49\t  - [ ] Return absolute worktree path\n50\t\n51\t- [ ] Task 3: Implement `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` (AC: #4, #5)\n52\t  - [ ] Find the branch matching `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-*` via `git branch --list`\n53\t  - [ ] Run `git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{epicId} --force`\n54\t  - [ ] Run `git branch -D {branch}` to delete the branch\n55\t  - [ ] Swallow errors if worktree or branch doesn't exist (idempotent, AC #5)\n56\t\n57\t- [ ] Task 4: Implement `listWorktrees()` (AC: #6, #7)\n58\t  - [ ] Run `git worktree list --porcelain` and parse output\n59\t  - [ ] Filter to entries whose branch starts with `codeharness/epic-`\n60\t  - [ ] Extract epicId from branch name pattern `codeharness/epic-{epicId}-{slug}`\n61\t  - [ ] Return `WorktreeInfo[]` sorted by epicId\n62\t\n63\t- [ ] Task 5: Implement `detectOrphans()` (AC: #8)\n64\t  - [ ] Call `listWorktrees()` to get all codeharness worktrees\n65\t  - [ ] Check each worktree path for a `.codeharness/lane-state.json` file\n66\t  - [ ] If lane-state.json doesn't exist or has no active PID, mark as orphan\n67\t  - [ ] Return orphaned `WorktreeInfo[]`\n68\t\n69\t- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#11)\n70\t  - [ ] Test: createWorktree creates branch and worktree, returns path\n71\t  - [ ] Test: createWorktree cleans up stale branch before re-creating\n72\t  - [ ] Test: createWorktree throws WorktreeError with stderr on git failure\n73\t  - [ ] Test: createWorktree cleans up partial state on failure\n74\t  - [ ] Test: cleanupWorktree removes worktree and branch\n75\t  - [ ] Test: cleanupWorktree is idempotent (no error when nothing exists)\n76\t  - [ ] Test: listWorktrees returns only codeharness-prefixed worktrees\n77\t  - [ ] Test: listWorktrees returns empty array when none exist\n78\t  - [ ] Test: detectOrphans identifies worktrees without active process\n79\t  - [ ] Test: branch names use codeharness/ prefix (NFR12)\n80\t  - [ ] Test: all error messages include stderr from git\n81\t\n82\t## Dev Notes\n83\t\n84\t### Architecture Constraints\n85\t\n86\t- **Architecture Decision 1** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Each parallel epic gets its own git worktree on a dedicated branch. The worktree manager handles the full lifecycle: create -> execute -> merge -> validate -> cleanup. This story covers create, cleanup, list, and orphan detection. Merge is deferred to Story 18-1.\n87\t- **Worktree Operations Pattern**: All git operations MUST use `child_process.execSync` for atomic git commands (create branch, add worktree). Use `child_process.exec` with timeout for potentially slow operations. Capture stderr for error reporting. Clean up on failure.\n88\t- **Branch naming**: `codeharness/` prefix prevents collision with user branches (NFR12).\n89\t- **Worktree location**: `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{N}` -- temporary, cleaned up after merge.\n90\t\n91\t### Key Files to Create\n92\t\n93\t| File | Purpose |\n94\t|------|---------|\n95\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Git worktree lifecycle module |\n96\t| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Unit tests |\n97\t\n98\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n99\t\n100\t| File | Why |\n101\t|------|-----|\n102\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig` interface -- has `isolation: 'worktree' \\| 'none'`. Worktree manager is used when `isolation === 'worktree'`. |\n103\t| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | Pattern reference for registry modules with interfaces + error class. Follow the same module structure. |\n104\t| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | Pattern reference for `appendFileSync`/`mkdirSync` file operations, `node:fs` imports, test patterns. |\n105\t| `src/lib/session-manager.ts` | Pattern reference for `child_process` usage in this codebase. |\n106\t\n107\t### Implementation Patterns\n108\t\n109\t**Git command execution:**\n110\t```typescript\n111\timport { execSync } from 'node:child_process';\n112\t\n113\t// Atomic git commands — use execSync\n114\texecSync(`git branch ${branchName} ${mainBranch}`, {\n115\t  cwd: projectDir,\n116\t  stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],  // capture stderr\n117\t});\n118\t\n119\t// Parse git worktree list --porcelain output:\n120\t// worktree /path/to/worktree\n121\t// HEAD abc123\n122\t// branch refs/heads/codeharness/epic-17-worktree-manager\n123\t// (blank line)\n124\t```\n125\t\n126\t**Error handling:**\n127\t```typescript\n128\ttry {\n129\t  execSync(cmd, { cwd, stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });\n130\t} catch (err: unknown) {\n131\t  const stderr = (err as { stderr?: Buffer })?.stderr?.toString() ?? '';\n132\t  throw new WorktreeError(`Failed to create worktree: ${stderr}`, stderr);\n133\t}\n134\t```\n135\t\n136\t**Testing strategy:** Mock `execSync` with `vi.mock('node:child_process')`. Verify correct git commands are called with correct arguments. Test error paths by making mock throw with stderr buffer.\n137\t\n138\t### Previous Story (16-6) Intelligence\n139\t\n140\t- Story 16-6 completed the story flow execution. All 4779 tests pass. This is the first story in Epic 17 -- a new module with no modifications to existing files.\n141\t- Recent code patterns: TypeScript modules in `src/lib/`, tests colocated in `__tests__/`, ESM with `.js` import extensions, vitest test framework.\n142\t- Module pattern: export interfaces, export functions or class, export error class. JSDoc comments on all exports.\n143\t- The workflow engine already has `ExecutionConfig` parsed from YAML. The worktree manager will be consumed by the lane pool (Story 17-2) and the merge serialization (Story 18-1).\n144\t\n145\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n146\t\n147\t- **Merge operations** -- deferred to Story 18-1. This story has no `mergeWorktree()` method.\n148\t- **Lane pool integration** -- deferred to Story 17-2. The worktree manager is a standalone module.\n149\t- **Run command integration** -- deferred to Story 17-3.\n150\t- **TUI components** -- deferred to Epic 20.\n151\t\n152\t### Edge Cases\n153\t\n154\t- **Stale branch from crash**: If `codeharness/epic-17-slug` already exists when `createWorktree` is called, the previous run crashed. Clean up the stale state before re-creating (AC #9). Do not throw.\n155\t- **Worktree directory already exists on disk**: `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17` might exist from a crash. `git worktree add` will fail. Handle by removing the directory first.\n156\t- **Not a git repo**: `execSync` throws. Wrap in `WorktreeError` with descriptive message.\n157\t- **Branch name with special characters**: The `slug` parameter comes from epic names. Sanitize to `[a-z0-9-]` before using in branch name.\n158\t- **Concurrent createWorktree calls**: Two calls with different epicIds are safe (different branches, different paths). Two calls with the same epicId are a bug in the caller -- the second will hit the stale-cleanup path.\n159\t\n160\t### Project Structure Notes\n161\t\n162\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n163\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/` directories\n164\t- ESM modules -- use `.js` extensions in imports\n165\t- Build: `npm run build`\n166\t- Test: `npm test`\n167\t\n168\t### References\n169\t\n170\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 17.1]\n171\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 1 — Worktree Lifecycle Model]\n172\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Worktree Operations Pattern]\n173\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Architectural Boundaries — Worktree Manager]\n174\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR6, FR7, FR11]\n175\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#NFR1, NFR9, NFR12]\n176\t\n177\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n178\t## Verification Requirements\n179\t\n180\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/17-1-worktree-manager-proof.md)\n181\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n182\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n183\t\n184\t## Documentation Requirements\n185\t\n186\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n187\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/17-1-worktree-manager.md\n188\t\n189\t## Testing Requirements\n190\t\n191\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n192\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n193\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n194\t\n195\t## Dev Agent Record\n196\t\n197\t### Agent Model Used\n198\t\n199\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n200\t\n201\t### Debug Log References\n202\t\n203\t### Completion Notes List\n204\t\n205\t### File List\n206\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HkThmW1eF3XHtUVHViMjeW","session_id":"187035da-d60e-40cf-8aef-09e6134be246","uuid":"cd1266b3-1ff2-43a3-ac1c-21601f1ebd06","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:24:10.013Z"}
