{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HkThmW1eF3XHtUVHViMjeW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 17-1 is complete. Here's the summary:\n\n**Story:** 17-1 Worktree Manager\n**Status:** review\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` — `WorktreeManager` class with `createWorktree()`, `cleanupWorktree()`, `listWorktrees()`, `detectOrphans()`, plus `WorktreeInfo` interface and `WorktreeError` class\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` — 25 unit tests\n\n**Test results:** 4805 tests pass across 178 files (0 failures, 0 regressions). The 25 new tests cover all 11 acceptance criteria.\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- All git commands use `execSync` with `stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe']` for stderr capture\n- Branch prefix `codeharness/epic-` prevents collision with user branches (NFR12)\n- Stale state from crashes is cleaned up before re-creating (AC #9)\n- Partial state is cleaned up on failure (AC #10)\n- All catch blocks have `// IGNORE:` comments per NFR3 boundary enforcement\n- Slug sanitization strips non-`[a-z0-9-]` characters\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Boundary test enforcement:** The codebase has a boundary test (`__tests__/boundaries.test.ts`) that requires all `catch` blocks to have `// IGNORE:` comments. This was not mentioned in the story's Dev Notes. I hit this on the first full suite run and had to add 11 `// IGNORE:` comments.\n- **Test expectation error:** Initial test for numeric sorting had the expected array in wrong order (`['10', '20', '3']` instead of `['3', '10', '20']`). Fixed immediately.\n- **No workarounds or tech debt added.**\n- **Observation:** The `createdAt` field on `WorktreeInfo` is set to `new Date()` at list time, not the actual worktree creation time. `git worktree list --porcelain` doesn't output creation timestamps. If accurate creation times are needed later, th