{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TYuLXKf4d7RFo7i8JzVmTn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 7)\n2\t\n3\t## Prior Sessions (Summary)\n4\t\n5\tSessions 1-3 completed stories 16-1, 16-2, 16-3. Key recurring issues:\n6\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path incorrect (actual: `_bmad/config.yaml`)\n7\t- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` broken due to pre-existing stats.test.ts failure\n8\t- AGENTS.md consistently missing new file entries\n9\t- Pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files\n10\t\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — create-story (2026-04-03T18:05)\n14\t\n15\t- New cross-module dependency: workflow engine will import from `state.ts` (harness state) for the first time — architecturally sound per Decision 7 but novel coupling.\n16\t- Risk: `projectDir` resolution unclear — engine config has `sprintStatusPath` but no explicit `projectDir`. Dev agent needs to determine resolution strategy.\n17\t- All 8 ACs tagged `test-provable`.\n18\t\n19\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 1, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 6, Write: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n20\t\n21\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — dev-story (2026-04-03T18:12)\n22\t\n23\t- Engine hardcodes `testResults: null` in all output contracts — flag propagation won't activate in production until a future story adds test result parsing from agent output. Logic is tested via contract mutation.\n24\t- Workaround: Tests use `writeOutputContract` mock interception to mutate contract object in-place past `readonly` interface. Couples to implementation detail.\n25\t- Tech debt: `readStateWithBody` returns mutable `HarnessState` — flag mutation relies on this mutability.\n26\t- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n27\t\n28\tToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 13, Edit: 11, Grep: 7). 7 unique files, 13 reads (workflow-engine.ts 5x, workflow-engine.test.ts 5x). No redundancy.\n29\t\n30\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — code-review (2026-04-03T18:20)\n31\t\n32\t- HIGH: Test AC#1 name claimed to test positive flag-setting but actually tested null/no-op path. Fixed.\n33\t- HIGH: Duplicate AC#7 test names. Fixed with AC#7b rename.\n34\t- MEDIUM: Bare catch block in `propagateVerifyFlags` swallowed error details. Fixed.\n35\t- LOW (not fixed): Tests rely on in-place mutation of contract object inside mock. Coupling risk.\n36\t- LOW (not fixed): No integration test for AC#6 (cross-module verify reads engine-set flags).\n37\t- Coverage: 96.59% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n38\t- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n39\t\n40\tToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 9, Edit: 4, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 7 unique files, 9 reads. No redundancy.\n41\t\n42\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — verify (2026-04-03T18:25)\n43\t\n44\t- ALL_PASS: 8/8 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n45\t- Verification gap: AC#6 proof is structural (confirms same field names read) — no E2E integration test.\n46\t- `codeharness verify` warning about missing exec-plan — informational only.\n47\t- 2 pre-existing lint warnings (prefer-const, unused error variable).\n48\t- Build, tests, lint, coverage all pass.\n49\t\n50\tToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 3, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. Coverage run duplicated with test run.\n51\t\n52\t---\n53\t\n54\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — create-story (2026-04-03T17:39)\n55\t\n56\t- No config.yaml found at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — workflow references it but doesn't exist. Not critical.\n57\t- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent per instruction. Still shows backlog.\n58\t- No web research needed — pure node:fs/node:path module.\n59\t- `attempts` field gap — TaskContext doesn't include retry count. Telemetry will have `attempts: null` until future story extends TaskContext.\n60\t\n61\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundanc