{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016VBFnDGg28kStQFMqQGXLu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport type { WorkflowState, TaskCheckpoint } from './workflow-state.js';\n2\t\n3\t// --- Types ---\n4\t\n5\t/** Session boundary mode as defined in workflow YAML schema. */\n6\texport type SessionBoundary = 'fresh' | 'continue';\n7\t\n8\t/** Key that uniquely identifies a task+story combination for session lookup. */\n9\texport interface SessionLookupKey {\n10\t  taskName: string;\n11\t  storyKey: string;\n12\t}\n13\t\n14\t// --- Functions ---\n15\t\n16\t/**\n17\t * Resolve the session ID to use for a dispatch call.\n18\t *\n19\t * - `fresh`: always returns undefined (new session).\n20\t * - `continue`: returns the most recent session ID for the task+story pair,\n21\t *    or undefined if none exists (first invocation falls back to fresh).\n22\t *\n23\t * Does NOT cache — always reads from the supplied WorkflowState for crash-recovery safety.\n24\t */\n25\texport function resolveSessionId(\n26\t  boundary: SessionBoundary,\n27\t  key: SessionLookupKey,\n28\t  state: WorkflowState,\n29\t): string | undefined {\n30\t  if (boundary === 'fresh') {\n31\t    return undefined;\n32\t  }\n33\t\n34\t  if (boundary !== 'continue') {\n35\t    // Defensive: unknown boundary value treated as fresh (safe default).\n36\t    return undefined;\n37\t  }\n38\t\n39\t  return getLastSessionId(state, key.taskName, key.storyKey);\n40\t}\n41\t\n42\t/**\n43\t * Record a session ID on a new TaskCheckpoint in the workflow state.\n44\t *\n45\t * Returns a **new** WorkflowState (does not mutate the input).\n46\t *\n47\t * Appends a new checkpoint entry with `session_id`, `task_name`, `story_key`,\n48\t * and `completed_at` (set to current time). The workflow engine (story 5-1)\n49\t * may enrich the checkpoint with additional fields after creation.\n50\t *"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M4NenhzW72RWGSvvu339mv","session_id":"187035da-d60e-40cf-8aef-09e6134be246