{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ays7koJRFG2deh9a5szXXS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 7)\n2\t\n3\t## Prior Sessions (Summary)\n4\t\n5\tSessions 1-3 completed stories 16-1, 16-2, 16-3. Key recurring issues:\n6\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path incorrect (actual: `_bmad/config.yaml`)\n7\t- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` broken due to pre-existing stats.test.ts failure\n8\t- AGENTS.md consistently missing new file entries\n9\t- Pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files\n10\t\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — create-story (2026-04-03T18:05)\n14\t\n15\t- New cross-module dependency: workflow engine will import from `state.ts` (harness state) for the first time — architecturally sound per Decision 7 but novel coupling.\n16\t- Risk: `projectDir` resolution unclear — engine config has `sprintStatusPath` but no explicit `projectDir`. Dev agent needs to determine resolution strategy.\n17\t- All 8 ACs tagged `test-provable`.\n18\t\n19\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 1, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 6, Write: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n20\t\n21\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — dev-story (2026-04-03T18:12)\n22\t\n23\t- Engine hardcodes `testResults: null` in all output contracts — flag propagation won't activate in production until a future story adds test result parsing from agent output. Logic is tested via contract mutation.\n24\t- Workaround: Tests use `writeOutputContract` mock interception to mutate contract object in-place past `readonly` interface. Couples to implementation detail.\n25\t- Tech debt: `readStateWithBody` returns mutable `HarnessState` — flag mutation relies on this mutability.\n26\t- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n27\t\n28\tToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 13, Edit: 11, Grep: 7). 7 unique files, 13 reads (workflow-engine.ts 5x, workflow-engine.test.ts 5x). No redundancy.\n29\t\n30\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — code-review (2026-04-03T18:20)\n31\t\n32\t- HIGH: Test AC#1 name claimed to test positive flag-setting but actually tested null/no-op path. Fixed.\n33\t- HIGH: Duplicate AC#7 test names. Fixed with AC#7b rename.\n34\t- MEDIUM: Bare catch block in `propagateVerifyFlags` swallowed error details. Fixed.\n35\t- LOW (not fixed): Tests rely on in-place mutation of contract object inside mock. Coupling risk.\n36\t- LOW (not fixed): No integration test for AC#6 (cross-module verify reads engine-set flags).\n37\t- Coverage: 96.59% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n38\t- 4747 tests pass, 0 failures.\n39\t\n40\tToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 9, Edit: 4, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 7 unique files, 9 reads. No redundancy.\n41\t\n42\t### 16-4-verify-flag-propagation — verify (2026-04-03T18:25)\n43\t\n44\t- ALL_PASS: 8/8 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n45\t- Verification gap: AC#6 proof is structural (confirms same field names read) — no E2E integration test.\n46\t- `codeharness verify` warning about missing exec-plan — informational only.\n47\t- 2 pre-existing lint warnings (prefer-const, unused error variable).\n48\t- Build, tests, lint, coverage all pass.\n49\t\n50\tToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 3, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. Coverage run duplicated with test run.\n51\t\n52\t---\n53\t\n54\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — create-story (2026-04-03T17:39)\n55\t\n56\t- No config.yaml found at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — workflow references it but doesn't exist. Not critical.\n57\t- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent per instruction. Still shows backlog.\n58\t- No web research needed — pure node:fs/node:path module.\n59\t- `attempts` field gap — TaskContext doesn't include retry count. Telemetry will have `attempts: null` until future story extends TaskContext.\n60\t\n61\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 3, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files, 10 total reads. No redundancy.\n62\t\n63\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — dev-story (2026-04-03T17:44)\n64\t\n65\tNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 18/18 tests pass, 26/26 existing tests pass.\n66\t\n67\tToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Edit: 8, Write: 2). 5 unique files, 5 total reads. No redundancy.\n68\t\n69\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — code-review (2026-04-03T17:55)\n70\t\n71\t- HIGH: `clearNullTaskRegistry` JSDoc claims it re-registers built-in handlers but does not. Fixed.\n72\t- MEDIUM: `readTelemetryForEpic` defaulted to `process.cwd()` — made `projectDir` required.\n73\t- MEDIUM: `TestResultsSummary` duplicated `TestResults` type. Fixed with type alias.\n74\t- MEDIUM: Unused imports in test. Fixed.\n75\t- MEDIUM: null-task-registry.test.ts re-registered fake no-op instead of real handler. Fixed.\n76\t- MEDIUM (pre-existing): stats.test.ts assertion mismatch. Fixed.\n77\t- LOW (not fixed): `cost ?? null` is dead code (cost is never undefined).\n78\t- LOW (not fixed): Unnecessary optional chain on `contract?.acceptanceCriteria`.\n79\t- Coverage: 96.58% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n80\t- 4737 tests pass, 0 failures.\n81\t\n82\tToken Report: 35 tool calls (Bash: 20, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 13 reads. Ran coverage 3 times.\n83\t\n84\t### 16-3-telemetry-writer — verify (2026-04-03T18:06)\n85\t\n86\t- ALL_PASS: 10/10 ACs verified with test and code evidence.\n87\t- `codeharness verify` failed on documentation gate: AGENTS.md missing entries for telemetry-writer.ts and null-task-registry.ts. Not an AC issue.\n88\t- Coverage: telemetry-writer.ts 100% Stmts, 93.75% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines.\n89\t- Branch gap: line 86 catch block empty path in readTelemetryForEpic uncovered (minor).\n90\t- 30 pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files.\n91\t\n92\tToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 4, Write: 1). 4 unique files. No redundancy.\n93\t\n94\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — create-story (2026-04-03T16:39)\n95\t\n96\t- Config file at `_bmad/config.yaml` not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` as workflow implied\n97\t- No `project-context.md` exists in repo — skipped\n98\t- Decomposed bundled epic ACs into 11 separate ACs for testability\n99\t- Added ACs #9 (flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity), #10 (agent: null), #11 (scope: per-epic) — implied by architecture but not explicit in epic\n100\t- Risk: `additionalProperties: false` in schema requires careful extension\n101\t- Risk: `oneOf` for flow/story_flow mutual exclusivity may be complex with Ajv — simpler to validate in TypeScript\n102\t- All 11 ACs tagged `test-provable`\n103\t\n104\tToken Report: 23 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n105\t\n106\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — dev-story (2026-04-03T16:48)\n107\t\n108\t- Pre-existing test failure: `commands/__tests__/stats.test.ts` — unrelated to this story\n109\t- Pre-existing TS errors in `run.test.ts`, `issue.test.ts`, `verdict-parser.test.ts` — unrelated\n110\t- Used Python script for bulk-replace of ~60 inline workflow objects in `workflow-engine.test.ts` with `makeWorkflow()` wrappers\n111\t- Schema vs code enforcement: `flow`/`story_flow` mutual exclusivity enforced in parser code, not JSON Schema `oneOf` (draft-07 creates confusing errors)\n112\t- `execution` object has `additionalProperties: false` — future config additions require schema changes\n113\t- 4676 tests passed, 1 pre-existing failure\n114\t\n115\tToken Report: 33 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 11, Edit: 15, Grep: 5, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 14 total reads. No redundancy.\n116\t\n117\t### 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser — code-review (2026-04-03T16:57)\n118\t\n119\t- HIGH: `resolveHierarchicalFlow` accepted arbitrary types without validation — could produce malformed objects. Fixed with `resolveExecutionConfig()` and `normalizeFlowArray()`.\n120\t- MEDIUM: Operator precedence issue in `workflow-parser.ts`