{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Envf2jhF6f8nhmBkSnCYGK","type":"tool_result","content":"6150\t- **`workflow-engine.ts` read fatigue:** This file was read 4-5 times per phase by code-review and dev subagents. The file is growing and subagents cannot retain its full content.\n6151\t\n6152\t---\n6153\t\n6154\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n6155\t\n6156\t### Patterns to Repeat\n6157\t\n6158\t1. **Session issues log as retro input** — concrete, timestamped, per-subagent data made this retro factual rather than subjective\n6159\t2. **Code review before verify** — HIGH bugs in 16-6 (wrong mock event type) were caught before they could pollute verification evidence\n6160\t3. **Small stories complete fast** — 16-6 proves that well-scoped stories with clear ACs can go from spec to verified in 20 minutes\n6161\t\n6162\t### Patterns to Avoid\n6163\t\n6164\t1. **Running coverage/lint twice in verify** — subagents should run once and parse the output correctly the first time. The verify instructions should specify exact commands with filters.\n6165\t2. **Re-reading large files repeatedly** — `workflow-engine.ts` needs to be split, or subagents need targeted read ranges instead of full-file reads\n6166\t3. **Ignoring broken infrastructure** — the `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` bug was known since session 1 and burned cycles in every session. Should have been fixed as a tech debt story.\n6167\t4. **No fast path for trivial stories** — a 2-line change should not require 4 full subagent phases\n6168\t\n6169\t---\n6170\t\n6171\t## 7. Action Items\n6172\t\n6173\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n6174\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n6175\t| 1 | Fix `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` — broken by stats.test.ts failure | HIGH | Next session |\n6176\t| 2 | Add proof format spec (`## AC N:` not `### AC N:`) to create-story template | HIGH | Tooling |\n6177\t| 3 | Fix `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path reference in workflow — should be `_bmad/config.yaml` | MEDIUM | Tooling |\n6178\t| 4 | Investigate verify phase cost ($140 = 44.6%) — can coverage/lint runs be deduplicated? | MEDIUM | Architecture |\n6179\t| 5 | Consider \"small story\" fast path that skips create-story for trivial changes | LOW | Process |\n6180\t| 6 | Split `workflow-engine.ts` or provide subagent read guidance to reduce redundant reads | LOW | Tech debt |\n6181\t| 7 | Create `project-context.md` so subagents stop reporting it missing | LOW | Documentation |\n6182\t\n6183\t---\n6184\t\n6185\t## Session Scorecard\n6186\t\n6187\t| Metric | Value |\n6188\t|--------|-------|\n6189\t| Stories completed | 1 (16-6) |\n6190\t| Epic completed | Epic 16 (final story) |\n6191\t| Total ACs verified | 6/6 (100%) |\n6192\t| HIGH bugs caught by review | 1 |\n6193\t| MEDIUM bugs caught by review | 2 |\n6194\t| Tests added | 12 (4768 -> 4780) |\n6195\t| Coverage | 96.61% |\n6196\t| Session cost | ~$7.00 |\n6197\t| Cost per story | $7.00 |\n6198\t| Retries | 0 |\n6199\t| Session duration | ~20 minutes |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QpvhZkSuAkJv9GMiaX49oT","session_id":"187035da-d60e-40cf-8aef-09e6134be246","uuid":"27180dde-92c5-4685-987a-c18493090445","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:44:49.186Z"}
